## Output Schema

{{ output_schema }}

For every workflow pattern, provide:
- `description`: What the pattern does and when it occurs.
- `pain_point`: Why this is suboptimal or repetitive.
- `example_refs`: StepRef objects with `session_id` and `start_step_id` pointing to real occurrences. Optionally include `end_step_id` for multi-step ranges.

For every generated skill, provide:
- `name`: Kebab-case skill name (e.g., `test-driven-fix`).
- `description`: One-line trigger description for the YAML frontmatter.
- `skill_md_content`: Complete SKILL.md content with YAML frontmatter and markdown body.
- `rationale`: Why this skill would improve the user's workflow.

After patterns and skills, provide:
- `summary`: Narrative overview of the user's workflow and skill opportunities.
- `user_profile`: Brief description of the user's working style and preferences.